      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(cli): allow image generate input files",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n`openclaw infer image generate` currently cannot accept local input/reference images, even though the shared image generation runner already supports file-backed `inputImages` and `image edit` already exposes a repeatable `--file` option.\n\nThis leaves a CLI parity gap for workflows that generate a new image from reference files. Issue #91734 documents that the missing piece is the command/metadata wiring, not a new provider or runtime abstraction.\n\n## Summary\n\n- Add repeatable `--file` support to `openclaw infer image generate`.\n- Forward generation input files through the existing `runImageGenerate` file-backed `inputImages` path.\n- Update `image.generate` capability metadata, focused CLI tests, and infer docs.\n\nFixes #91734\n\n## Security / Privacy Notes\n\nThis keeps the change scoped to local CLI option wiring. It does not add new auth, network, secret, permission, storage, or external-write behavior.\n\nInput files use the existing image file read and MIME detection path already used by `image edit`, then flow into the existing `inputImages` provider request field.\n\n## Evidence\n\nValidation run locally on branch `shannon/issue-91734-image-generate-file` at head `e18bccf5a912f14eaab57eaea8797a80a46678eb`:\n\n```sh\npnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/cli/capability-cli.ts src/cli/capability-cli.test.ts docs/cli/infer.md\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/cli/capability-cli.test.ts\ngit diff --check\n```\n\nResults:\n\n- formatting: passed on 3 changed files\n- `src/cli/capability-cli.test.ts`: 99 tests passed\n- `git diff --check`: passed\n\nFocused behavior proof added in `src/cli/capability-cli.test.ts`:\n\n- invokes `capability image generate --file <png> --prompt ... --json`\n- verifies `generateImage` receives `inputImages`\n- verifies the generated input image keeps `fileName` and `mimeType`\n- verifies `capability inspect --name image.generate --json` reports `--file`\n",
